The use of graph contraction and independent random sample extractor also suggests that the paper may belong to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of graph connectivity and the mention of lower bounds suggest that the paper may also belong to the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of the wide applicability of the approaches suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of network science (cs.NE).
